<div class="a11y-pattern-content">
  <h1>Toggle Button Group Accessibility</h1>
  <h2>Best Practices</h2>
  <p>
    The toggle button group is not a form control; although it can be used
    within a form - like all buttons - it does not store and submit form data.
  </p>
  <p>
    The toggle button group is not a drop-in replacement for radios or
    checkboxes, nor does it operate like those.
  </p>
  <h2>Interaction Design</h2>
  <p>
    Even though a toggle button group is single-select or multi-select, like
    radios and checkboxes respectively, they do not share the exact same
    interactions as radios and checkboxesâ€¦
  </p>
  <p>
    In a single select toggle group, pressing one button will unpress any
    currently pressed button in the group.
  </p>
  <p>
    In a multi select toggle group, pressing a button will have no effect on any
    of the other buttons in the group.
  </p>
  <h2>ARIA Reference</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <strong>aria-pressed</strong>
        </td>
        <td>
          Conveys whether the button is pressed or not (i.e true or false)
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
